The paper discusses the use of self-organizing maps (SOMs) for machine learning, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on supervised regression and classification, which falls under the category of machine learning. The datasets used in the evaluation are from geospatial image analysis, which falls under computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since SOMs are a type of artificial neural network, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses the development of a Python package, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible sub-category as well.
